From: PS4 Linux Baikal Port <noreply@ps4-linux>
Subject: [PATCH] amdgpu: v54 - source-only DP training pulse for Liverpool

After v53 confirmed the DP transmitter is fully and correctly
configured on Liverpool/Gladius (TX SETUP + SETUP_VSEMPH + ENABLE all
run with coherent args: UNIPHYA, 4 lanes, 270 MHz, DP mode), the
remaining missing step is **emitting actual DP training symbols on
the link**. Without TPS1/TPS2 on the wire, the MN864729 bridge has
nothing to lock its receiver onto — its cq_wait_set polls for DP
lane status indefinitely and times out at 3 seconds.

Stock CIK DP path emits TPS1/TPS2 from inside
amdgpu_atombios_dp_link_train, by calling
amdgpu_atombios_encoder_setup_dig_encoder with action codes:

  ATOM_ENCODER_CMD_DP_LINK_TRAINING_START    (0x08)
  ATOM_ENCODER_CMD_DP_LINK_TRAINING_PATTERN1 (0x09)
  ATOM_ENCODER_CMD_DP_LINK_TRAINING_PATTERN2 (0x0a)
  ATOM_ENCODER_CMD_DP_LINK_TRAINING_COMPLETE (0x0b)

Those source-side actions are independent of DPCD reads. They tell
the GPU's DIG encoder to drive specific bit patterns onto the four DP
lanes at the configured link rate. The kernel's DPCD-based trainer
interleaves them with sink readbacks to adjust voltage swing per
attempt, and that DPCD path is what fails on the PS4's fake-DP bridge
(which is why patch 0006 made link_train early-return).

This patch (v54) replaces the bare `return;` from patch 0006 with a
call to a new static helper amdgpu_atombios_dp_ps4_source_train that
emits the canonical training sequence with no DPCD reads:

  pr_info("ps4_atom: source-only DP training pulse START")
  setup_dig_encoder(LINK_TRAINING_START, 0)
  mdelay(5)
  setup_dig_encoder(LINK_TRAINING_PATTERN1, 0)
  mdelay(5)
  setup_dig_encoder(LINK_TRAINING_PATTERN2, 0)
  mdelay(5)
  setup_dig_encoder(LINK_TRAINING_COMPLETE, 0)
  mdelay(1)
  pr_info("ps4_atom: source-only DP training pulse COMPLETE")

Why this lives inside amdgpu_atombios_dp_link_train (vs directly in
amdgpu_atombios_encoder_setup_dig per Hermes' suggestion):

  - Maintains the semantic that "PS4 has a special link_train
    implementation" rather than scattering DP-specific logic in the
    DPMS path.
  - Encoder DPMS sequencing stays unchanged: TX ENABLE → link_train()
    → DP_VIDEO_ON → bridge_enable.
  - Easier to evolve the trainer body later (e.g., hold TPS2 during
    bridge_enable for v55) without touching DPMS.

Patch 0006's behavior changes from "return immediately for Liverpool"
to "source-only train, no DPCD reads". The early-return comment is
updated; the structure stays the same so it's a small diff.

mdelay between phases gives the bridge time to observe each pattern.
DP spec requires CR_DONE within 100µs per attempt; 5ms dwell is
conservative for the PS4 fixed-config link.

Expected v54 trace markers in next boot:

  ps4_atom: floor dig_connector dp_clock=270000 dp_lane_count=4
  ps4_atom: AdjustDisplayPll v1.3 OUT r=0 freq=270000
  ps4_atom: SetPixelClock IN ... pll=1 ...
  ps4_atom: SetPixelClock OUT r=0
  ps4_atom: dig_encoder action=0x0c (DP_VIDEO_OFF)
  ps4_atom: dig_tx action=0 (DISABLE)
  ps4_atom: dig_encoder action=0x0f (SETUP)
  ps4_atom: dig_encoder action=0x10 (PANEL_MODE)
  ps4_atom: forcing TX SETUP + SETUP_VSEMPH before ENABLE
  ps4_atom: dig_tx action=10 (SETUP)
  ps4_atom: dig_tx action=11 (SETUP_VSEMPH)
  ps4_atom: dig_tx action=1 (ENABLE)
  ps4_atom: source-only DP training pulse START                       <- v54
  ps4_atom_table: [d=0] enter idx=0x... (DIGxEncoderControl) ps_size=24
    -> DP_LINK_TRAINING_START
  ... (5 ms delay, on link: TPS1 carrier)
  ps4_atom_table: [d=0] enter idx=0x... -> PATTERN1
  ... (5 ms delay)
  ps4_atom_table: [d=0] enter idx=0x... -> PATTERN2
  ... (5 ms delay)
  ps4_atom_table: [d=0] enter idx=0x... -> COMPLETE
  ps4_atom: source-only DP training pulse COMPLETE                    <- v54
  ps4_atom: dig_encoder action=0x0d (DP_VIDEO_ON)
  ps4_bridge_enable: BEGIN
  ps4_bridge_enable: cq_exec=20  (with the 3-s wait collapsed)

Outcomes:

  - cq_wait_set 3-s hang collapses + HDMI lights up → done. Promote
    v47/v49/v52/v53/v54 to permanent, clean up traces.
  - cq_wait_set still hangs but timing pattern differs (e.g., shrinks
    to ~1 s, or hangs at a different cq step) → bridge is seeing some
    link activity but training is incomplete. v55 candidates: hold
    TPS2 during bridge_enable instead of completing first; try
    PATTERN3/PATTERN4 (TPS3/TPS4 are required for higher rates but
    might be needed here too); increase mdelay; manually toggle
    voltage swing via SETUP_VSEMPH between PATTERN1 and PATTERN2.
  - cq_wait_set unchanged at 3 s → bridge is not waiting on link
    symbols at all; the issue is elsewhere (e.g., wrong UNIPHY block
    despite VBIOS object ID, or DCE clock-tree state still wrong).
    v55 fallback: dump bridge MN864729 internal status registers via
    cq_read at known offsets (0x60f8, 0x60f9 from prior agent
    analysis) right before/after the source-only train.

---
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/atombios_dp.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/atombios_dp.c
@@ -725,6 +725,45 @@
 	}
 }

+/* v54: Source-only DP training pulse for PS4 Liverpool/Gladius.
+ *
+ * Called from amdgpu_atombios_dp_link_train as a replacement for the
+ * standard DPCD-driven link trainer (which times out on the bridge's
+ * fake DPCD). Emits the canonical sequence of source-side ATOM
+ * encoder actions — LINK_TRAINING_START → PATTERN1 → PATTERN2 →
+ * COMPLETE — without any DPCD reads. This puts real bit patterns
+ * (TPS1 then TPS2) on the GPU's DP TX output so the MN864729 bridge
+ * has something to lock onto when its cq_wait_set polls for lane
+ * status. After v53 confirmed TX SETUP/SETUP_VSEMPH/ENABLE all run
+ * with coherent args (UNIPHYA, 4 lanes, 270 MHz, DP mode), this is
+ * the missing "actually drive symbols on the link" step.
+ *
+ * mdelay between each phase gives the bridge time to observe the
+ * pattern. Standard DP requires CR_DONE in 100us per attempt; a 5ms
+ * dwell is conservative for the PS4 fixed-config link. */
+static void amdgpu_atombios_dp_ps4_source_train(struct drm_encoder *encoder)
+{
+	pr_info("ps4_atom: source-only DP training pulse START\n");
+
+	amdgpu_atombios_encoder_setup_dig_encoder(encoder,
+		ATOM_ENCODER_CMD_DP_LINK_TRAINING_START, 0);
+	mdelay(5);
+
+	amdgpu_atombios_encoder_setup_dig_encoder(encoder,
+		ATOM_ENCODER_CMD_DP_LINK_TRAINING_PATTERN1, 0);
+	mdelay(5);
+
+	amdgpu_atombios_encoder_setup_dig_encoder(encoder,
+		ATOM_ENCODER_CMD_DP_LINK_TRAINING_PATTERN2, 0);
+	mdelay(5);
+
+	amdgpu_atombios_encoder_setup_dig_encoder(encoder,
+		ATOM_ENCODER_CMD_DP_LINK_TRAINING_COMPLETE, 0);
+	mdelay(1);
+
+	pr_info("ps4_atom: source-only DP training pulse COMPLETE\n");
+}
+
 void amdgpu_atombios_dp_link_train(struct drm_encoder *encoder,
 			    struct drm_connector *connector)
 {
@@ -741,9 +780,14 @@
 	 * itself.  Kernel-side DP link training never completes clock
 	 * recovery on this hardware (5x retries → fail), and the bridge's
 	 * pre_enable/enable callbacks are what actually program the link.
-	 * Skip kernel link training so amdgpu modeset can proceed. */
-	if (adev->asic_type == CHIP_LIVERPOOL || adev->asic_type == CHIP_GLADIUS)
+	 * Skip the DPCD-driven trainer but DO emit a source-only training
+	 * pulse (TPS1/TPS2 patterns on the GPU's DP TX output) so the bridge
+	 * has something to lock its receiver onto. v54: previously this
+	 * branch was a bare `return;` (patch 0006). */
+	if (adev->asic_type == CHIP_LIVERPOOL || adev->asic_type == CHIP_GLADIUS) {
+		amdgpu_atombios_dp_ps4_source_train(encoder);
 		return;
+	}

 	if (!amdgpu_encoder->enc_priv)
 		return;
